column7: SYMPTOM: 1) WIRE LIST SHOWS BOTH WIRES BEING CONNECTED TO “RESET-1,” BK/22 WIRE SHOULD BE CONNECTED TO “RESET-2.” 2) NOTCH REFERENCE ON SWITCH END OF CABLE IS NOT POINTING TO CORRECT LOCATION, CAUSING CONFUSION IN MANUFACTURING.  ROOT CAUSE: 1) TYPO WHEN DRAWING WAS REDRAWN ON REV. B (REV. A IS CORRECT). 2) NOTCH REFERENCE USED TO SHOW CORRECT LOCATION, BUT VENDOR CHANGED. NOTCH IS NOW ON OTHER SIDE OF SWITCH.  SOLUTION: 1) FIX WIRE LIST SO THAT BK/22 WIRE IS CONNECTED TO “RESET-2.” 2) MANUFACTURING DOES NOT NEED OR USE NOTCH REFERENCE, REMOVE NOTE.
